oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Magazine pouch for Colt Model 1911
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This small pouch held two magazines of .45 caliber ammuntion of the Model 1911 Colt Automatic Pistol, the standard side arm of the United States military in World War I. This pouch belonged to Cpl. Roy R. Stephens, Co. H, 5th Inf. Regt.
